{"questionId":"33030827","questionHtml":"<p>The following diagram shows triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ABC</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BC</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AC</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></math>.<br><br></p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/a5f74c803ef8701dbc2afcf06454489a98c61151.png\" width=\"704\" height=\"249\"><br>Find the exact value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math>, giving your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>p</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mi>q</mi></mfrac></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to substitute into cosine rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo></math> &nbsp; </strong></em>OR&nbsp; &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>27</mn><mn>48</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br>attempt to use&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>27</mn><mn>48</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>75</mn><mn>96</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mo>±</mo></mfenced><msqrt><mfrac><mn>75</mn><mn>96</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>32</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br></strong></em><strong>Note: </strong>The final answer must be positive.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]<br></strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33030827","referenceCode":"24N.1.AHL.TZ0.4","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"The following diagram shows triangle ABC, where AB=4 cm, BC=6 cm, AC=5 cm and AB^C=2θ. Find the exact value of cos θ, giving your answer in the form p2q, where p, q∈ℤ+.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"4","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Pythagorean identity, double angles"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}